import java.io.*; // for File I/O and InputStreams to read directories 1-by-1 (FileWalker) & BufferedReader class java_43229_FileScanner_A03 for reading files in chunks(TextScanner). Also, it contains utilities like createNewFile() method of Files library which is not available from Java Standard Library.
import java.util.*; // For List and Scanner classes to use ArrayList or read input provided by user (UserInput) & BufferedReader class for reading the file in chunks(TextScanner). 1-by line scanning mode has been used with FileWalker utility method, where each word is a list item added into arrayList.
import java.util.stream.*; // Stream API to use stream methods and functional interfaces (like map(), filter() etc.). It's optional as we are only reading file in chunks anyway so this won’t be very beneficial but it will make our code more readable by avoiding explicit loop constructs over lists/arrays elements like for-each do.
import java.nio.*; // For Path and FileSystem to get access on directories or files (FileAccessor) & BufferedReader class used when reading a file in chunks(TextScanner). 1 line at the time is read into buffer which gets filtered by Stream API after that, further processed as per business logic.
import java.security.*; // For MessageDigest to generate hash of user's entered word (PasswordHashGenerator) & input sanitizer for preventing SQL Injection attacks with PreparedStatement used in real-world applications and this will not be very necessary if we only doing file reading/writing work instead using InputStreamReader or BufferedReaders.
import java.nio.file.*; // For Paths, Files etc to get access on directories & files (FileAccessor). 1 line at a time is read into buffer which gets filtered by Stream API after that further processed as per business logic and written back in file using PrintWriter or FileOutputStream/Files methods provided for this purpose only.
import java.util.*; // For List, ArrayList etc to use when manipulating data (ManipulationData). 1 line at a time is read into buffer which gets filtered by Stream API after that further processed as per business logic and written back in file using PrintWriter or FileOutputStream/Files methods provided for this purpose only if we are not performing any security sensitive operation.